			<div id="PrivacyPolicyContent" class="StyledParagraphComponent">
	<p>Pillow Talk Australia PTY LTD (trading as &ldquo;Pillow Talk&rdquo;) recognises the importance of protecting the privacy and rights of individuals and is committed to protecting your privacy Online. We use a variety of security measures to protect your information, including secure servers, firewalls and encryption.  <br/> <br/> This is our privacy policy and it outlines how we collect and manage your personal information.  Please read the following policy to understand the limited information that Pillow Talk collects and how it is used. <br/> <br/> Please note, by accessing or using pillowtalk.com.au you agree to the terms of our privacy policy and website terms and conditions.  If you do not agree to these terms, please do not use or access our website. <br/> <br/> If you have any questions regarding our privacy policy, please feel free to contact us by email at <span style="font-size: 14px; font-family: Georgia; font-style: italic; color: #ff3b57;"><a href="mailto:privacy@ptpl.com.au?subject=PRIVACY POLICY QUERY">privacy@ptpl.com.au</a></span></p>    <h3>What do we mean by your &ldquo;personal information&rdquo;?</h3>    <p>When referred to in this policy, the term &ldquo;personal information&rdquo; includes any information that can be used to personally identify you.  This could include your name, address, phone number, email address, and date of birth.  If the information that we collect can personally identify you or you can be reasonably identified from it, we classify it as personal information. <br/> <!--</p--></p>   <h3>How do we collect your personal information?</h3>       <p>We will collect your personal information directly from you and we may collect it in the following ways: <br/> <br/> i.	through your access and use of our website; <br/> ii. during conversations between you and our representatives; <br/> iii. when you complete an application or purchase order ask for a quote to be prepared<br/> iv. when you contact us for further information or register your details on our website; <br/> v.	your participation in surveys and other types of research; <br/> vi. when you enter a promotion, sweepstake, or contest hosted by Pillow Talk;<br/> vii. when you subscribe to our mailing list; or<br/> viii.	when you submit a job application or r&eacute;sum&eacute; <br/> <br/> We may also collect personal information from third parties such as recruitment consultancies, credit reporting agencies, law enforcement agencies, and other government agencies.</p>    <h3>What type of personal information do we collect?</h3>   <p>We may collect the following types of personal information from you: <br/> <br/> ix. your name, residential mailing, email addresses and mobile number; <br/> x.	your date of birth, gender, age, purchase history, hobbies and interests; <br/> xi.	details of the products you have purchased from us or which you have enquired about, together with any additional information necessary to deliver those products and to respond to your enquiries; <br/> xii.	any additional information relating to you that you provide to us directly through our website or indirectly through use of our website or Online presence; and <br/> xiii.	any information you provide us through our customer service centre, customer surveys and competitions.</p>   <h3>What other information do we collect from you?</h3>   <p>To help us improve your Online experience at Pillow Talk we collect anonymous information about website activity.  We use this data to evaluate our website's performance and to improve the content we display to you.  <br/> <br/> To evaluate the effectiveness of our Online advertising, we may use third parties to collect statistical data. No personal information is collected on these occasions however we may log IP addresses (the electronic address of a computer connected to the internet) to analyse trends, track our users&rsquo; movements and to gather broad demographic information about our visitors.  <br/> <br/> Our website uses Google AdWords, Google Analytics, and the Google Display Network combined together to display Pillow Talk ads to you on other websites after you have visited our website.  In the industry, this practice is known as remarketing and is a tool that Google offers to businesses.  If you would like to know more about the remarketing program, you can find out more <a href="https://support.google.com/ads/answer/2662922?hl=en">here. </a> If you would like to opt-out of receiving advertising like this from Google, you can manage these settings by visiting the Google <a href="https://support.google.com/ads/answer/2662922?hl=en"> Ads Preferences Manager. </a><br/> <br/> To use some of our services, users are required to register as Pillow Talk Members.  Any information that we store about you as a Pillow Talk Member can be viewed and changed by you by logging in to the web site at <a href="/login">https://www.pillowtalk.com.au/login</a>.  Please note, any information that you provide to us via the Contact Us section is not retained after the query has been dealt with.</p>    <h3>Why do we collect, use and hold your personal information?</h3>   <p>Pillow Talk collects, uses and holds your personal information to better understand your needs as a customer and to help us provide you with better service. We collect, use and hold your personal information: <br/> <br/> xiv.	to complete a transaction in store or Online via our website; <br/> xv.	to deal with your queries or customer service issues promptly whether by email, telephone or mail; <br/> xvi.	to keep you up-to-date with products, services, events or promotions we think may be of particular interest through a variety of channels. You are able to &ldquo;opt-out&rdquo; from this activity at any time; <br/> xvii.	to enhance your customer experience Online and help us complete your transactions faster; <br/> xviii.	for planning, marketing or research purposes; <br/> xix.	to provide you with access to protected areas of our website; <br/> xx.	to conduct business processing functions including providing personal information to our contractors, service providers or other third parties eg. couriers or postal services.</p>    <h3>Who do we share your information with?</h3>   <p>Pillow Talk will not sell, rent, or lease your personally identifiable information to others other than as described in this Privacy Policy.  <br/> <br/> We may disclose your personal information to: <br/> <br/> xxi.	our employees, contractors or service providers for the purposes of operation of our website or our business, fulfilling requests by you, and to otherwise provide products and services to you including, without limitation, web hosting providers, IT systems administrators, mailing houses, couriers, payment processors, data entry service providers, electronic network administrators, debt collectors, and professional advisors such as accountants, solicitors, business advisors and consultants; <br/> xxii.	suppliers and other third parties with whom we have commercial relationships for business, marketing, and related purposes; and, <br/> xxiii.	to comply with any relevant law. <br/> Pillow Talk will only disclose your personal information when we believe, in good faith, that the disclosure is required by law and then only to appropriate regulatory authorities.   In the case of a breach of the terms and conditions of our website we reserve the right to provide the details of the offender to the appropriate Association/Client for any action they wish to take regarding the breach.  <br/> <br/> We do not provide your personal information to other organisations for the purposes of direct marketing.</p>      <h3>Direct Marketing Material</h3>   <p>At Pillow Talk we may send you direct marketing communications and information about our products and services that we consider may be of interest to you.  These communications may be sent in various forms, including mail, SMS, and email, in accordance with applicable marketing laws, such as the Spam Act 2003 (Cth).  You consent to us sending you those direct marketing communications by any of those methods.  <br/> <br/> All our email based services to our Members are opt-in and Members have the ability to opt-out (i.e. to suspend or cancel all marketing emails from the Pillow Talk site) at any time. This can be controlled by logging into the website and updating your preferences at <a href="/login">https://www.pillowtalk.com.au/login</a> or clicking the &ldquo;Unsubscribe&rdquo; link found at the bottom of all electronic newsletters that Pillow Talk send.  Alternatively if you would like to unsubscribe from receiving electronic newsletters please contact us at <span style="font-size: 14px;font-family: Georgia; font-style: italic; color: #ff3b57;"><a href="mailto:privacy@ptpl.com.au?subject=UNSUBSCRIBE ME">privacy@ptpl.com.au</a></span> and we will remove your details from our database.</p>    <h3>Credit Card Security</h3>   <p>We take credit card security extremely seriously and always endeavour to provide a safe and secure platform on which to conduct Online transactions.  Pillow Talk uses the industry standard Secure Sockets Layer (SSL) protocol which encrypts your credit card information as it is transmitted over the internet.  This encryption scrambles details such as credit card number, billing details and delivery address so that generally, other computers are unable to decipher the information, ensuring privacy and security. To make sure you are accessing a secure server, check that the URL starts with HTTPS rather than HTTP and look for the unbroken key or closed lock symbol located generally either at the bottom left or top right of your browser window eg.  <br/> <br/> For payments by credit card we accept only Visa and MasterCard through Verified by Visa&copy; and securecode&copy; respectively.  As a result, at Pillow Talk we only receive an authorisation code which is unique and not reusable and no credit card details are provided to us or held by us post transaction.</p>      <h3>What are cookies?</h3>   <p>Pillow Talk uses tracking technologies such as cookies which are used to recognise your browser each time it visits our website.  A cookie is a data file that some web sites write to your computer's hard drive for record keeping purposes.  Pillow Talk will create a temporary cookie on your computer if you log into our web site using your username and password or create a shopping basket.  This cookie is used to secure your connection to our web server. Once you log out of our web site or navigate to another web site, this cookie is automatically removed. The information stored in the cookie is a unique code that is generated by our server to keep track of your Online session at Pillow Talk.  No personal information is stored inside this cookie and it cannot be used to personally identify users beyond identifying their browser and date/time of visit.  However if you do not wish to receive any cookies from websites, you are able to set your browser to refuse them.  <br/> <br/> Chrome users can find information about disabling cookies <a href="https://support.google.com/accounts/answer/61416?hl=en">here. </a> <br/> Firefox users can find information about disabling cookies <a href="https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/enable-and-disable-cookies-website-preferences">here.  </a><br/> Internet Explorer users can find information about disabling cookies<a href="http://windows.microsoft.com/en-au/windows-vista/block-or-allow-cookies"> here.  </a><br/> Safari users can find information about disabling cookies <a href="http://support.apple.com/kb/index?page=search&amp;q=cookies%20safari">here. </a></p>   <h3>Links to Other Websites</h3>   <p>We may provide links to third party websites via www.pillowtalk.com.au which are provided solely as a convenience to you and are not operated by us.  These linked sites are not under our control and we do not accept responsibility for the conduct of companies linked from this website.  Pillow Talk is not responsible for any of these sites, their content or their usage of your personal information.</p>   <h3>Social Sharing</h3>   <p>Pillow Talk may offer social sharing features and other integrated tools (such as the Facebook &ldquo;Like&rdquo; button) on our website, which let you share actions you take on our website with other media, and vice versa.  The use of such features enables the sharing of information with your friends or the public, depending on the settings you have established with the entity that provides that particular social sharing feature.  The privacy settings of these social sites are neither moderated nor controlled by Pillow Talk and we do not accept responsibility for the conduct of these social sharing networks. For more information about the purpose and scope of data collection and processing in connection with social sharing networks, please visit the privacy policies of the entities that provide these features.</p>   <h3>How to Contact Us</h3>   <div>You have the right to access your records to verify or amend the personal information that we have on file by contacting us and making a formal request.  Please contact us as per the details below or email us at <span style="font-size: 14px;font-family: Georgia; font-style: italic; color: #ff3b57;"><a href="mailto:privacy@ptpl.com.au?subject=REQUESTING MY DATA">privacy@ptpl.com.au</a></span>  <br/> If you have any questions about Pillow Talk's privacy policy, any concerns, or a complaint regarding the treatment of your privacy or a possible breach of your privacy, please use the <a href="/sales-gifts/contact-us">contact link</a> on our website or contact our Privacy Officer using the details set out below. <br/> <br/> We will treat your requests or complaints confidentially and we will contact you within a reasonable time after receipt of your complaint to discuss your concerns and outline options regarding how they may be resolved. 